Others: Cameroon national team’s preparations for the 2025 Afcon Qualifiers have been disrupted due to players not reporting for camp in Douala.
The senior players are currently camping in Yaounde, while the U20 team has been training in Mbankomo and has been called up to train in Douala.
Cameroonian Football Federation (FECAFOOT) president Samuel Eto’o has called up the U20s to train, while waiting for the senior players to arrive.

FECAFOOT has taken measures to transport the players from their respective clubs to Douala, but some players have been taken out of the Federation's supervision and communicated to their respective clubs.
The instigators of these actions will be held accountable and will assume full responsibility for any damage they have caused to the country.
